**[1842, 02-15] Ms.A.1.2.12.2.28**

Davis, Edward Morris, to EPN; Philadelphia. Hope for peaceful abolition
of slavery; increased interest in Br. India question; Irish address. ...
{Bulk in {u}BAA{/u}, No. 119}

[Mentions Charles Dickens’ tour; fears he is being tinctured by
pro-slavery. Urges Pease to prevail on Mary Howitt to come out with some
anti-slavery work, as the time would be ripe for such a production. “Why
are not the abolitionists of G. Britain, Chartists Repealers & ultra
Democrats?”


